  "response": "The Vice Presidential debate between Democrat Tim Kaine and Republican Mike Pence took place on October 4, 2016. Political analysts and various news outlets had mixed opinions on who won the debate, but overall, many pundits and viewers felt that Mike Pence performed better, often citing his calm and composed demeanor compared to Tim Kaine's more aggressive style. Additionally, Pence was generally seen as more effective in defending then-presidential nominee Donald Trump against criticisms, which contributed to the perception that he won the debate. However, opinions on debate outcomes can be highly subjective and influenced by individual political biases.",
